<L>__{exterior patriot encampment acworth evening}
<A>__{grim. the most rudimentary of the encampments we've seen. rain pours. some of marion's men huddle under lean to's and quickly rigged tents that offer only partial protection from the cold rain. abner and scott do their best to keep a wet wood fire going. rev. oliver tries to cook. marion and gabriel ride up and dismount. marion joins rev. oliver.}
<C>__{marion}
<D>__{how many came back?}
<C>__{rev. oliver}
<D>__{about a hundred and twenty. less than a third.}
<A>__{marion nods. he and gabriel join some of the men under one of the lean to's.}
